  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\n\r\n`You're unauthorized to perform this operation` pop-up is shown while attempting to change PIN if biometric login was applied to this Keycard multiaccount or password was saved.\r\n\r\n#### Notes\r\n\r\nTo reproduce this issue, re-login is required after first enabling the biometric login/saving the passcode. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nCan change PIN\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n<img width=\"262\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-05-21 at 14 18 41\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67952253/119136038-72ffba00-ba3f-11eb-87b3-0bc38c9bfe1d.png\">\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Recover Keycard multiaccount\r\n2. Log out\r\n3. Enable biometric login / Save password (`Don't ask for card to sign in` checkbox)\r\n4. Log out and re-login\r\n5. Open Settings > Keycard > Change 6-digit passcode\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly 21/05\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS",
